channel.title: Frostys cache problem
channel.description:
I can't seem to get Frostys cache editor to work with my cache, not sure why though.
I'm trying to fix some items of the server which have been set as stacked but can't access the items?
I get an error whenever I try to select Items.
[IMG]http://image.prntscr.com/image/7a3f7169cae54651b29e4eee94579b13.png[/img]

item.title: Frostys cache problem
item.dc:creator: @Roar337 Roar337
item.description:
@Roar337 wrote:

A cache is a cache is a cache… wait… no it’s not! Unfortunately as much as a server changes from revision to revision so does the cache! You need a cache editor who’s cache loading class is the same as the cache you are trying to load (most often due to op code mismatching).

To fix this you could probably find in your client or server where cache is being loaded as item definitions and replace frosty’s class with yours and fix the errors.
